==English==
=== Etymology ===
First attested 1553, from {{Gr.}} '''''apophthegma''''' "something clearly spoken", from [[apo-]], "[[from]]" + [[phthengesthai]], "to [[say]], [[utter]]."

=== Pronunciations ===
*{{AHD|ăpə-thĕm′}}
*{{SAMPA|/{p."E.TEm/}}
*{{IPA|/æp.ˈɛ.θɛm/}}

===Noun===
'''apothegm''' ''or'' '''apophthegm''' (Brit.)

#a short [[witty]] [[instructive]] [[saying]]; an [[aphorism]] or [[maxim]].

====Usage notes====
*Not to be confused with the [[homonym]] ''[[apothem]]''.

